accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: The contents of Series 3 must be reviewed for restricted employee records prior to use; these records are closed to research for 75 years from date of record creation. Series 3 is closed to research for 75 years from date of record creation.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Human Resource Services at The George Washington University is made up of four divisions. These are Benefit Services, Employee Relations, Staffing and Compensation Services and Records and Dat Management. At one point the Records and Benefits office was a part personnel services at the University This note was written in 2005.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in the collection include personnel, fringe benefits, and policy files from 1954 to 1992.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized in three series: General files, Office files, and Personnel files.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of correspondence, manuals, brochures, applications, regulations memorandums, forms, a poster, a study, and other files. They range in date from 1954 to 1992. Th materials concern employee benefits; sick and annual leave; affirmative action; dental insurance tuition benefits; regulations governing administrative assistants and research personnel; wage pric and hiring freezes; accident and injury claims; salaries; the Budget Office; the Office of Budgetin and Planning; education benefits; the credit union; the Faculty/Employee Assistance Program; healt care plans, and filling vacancies.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains files about fringe benefits as well as the general management of personnel, salaries, and benefits at the university and hospital. The material dates from 1957-87, with the bulk being from around 1979-1987.
This series has a paper container list in the reading room, please ask staff for assistance.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains personnel records from employees at GW during World War II. Included are th personal files of workers at the Allegany laboratory. These files contain photographs of workers correspondence, term dates, and other information relating to their positions at the University These materials range in date from 1940-1950.
